It seems like you&#39;re using `@Embedded` to handle a `jsonb` column parser. 

&gt; The JPA annotation @Embedded is used to embed a type into another entity.

Embedding entity columns and mapping of to a single database table. You can refer to this [doc](https://www.baeldung.com/jpa-embedded-embeddable) for more info.


Your case if you&#39;re using Hibernate 6, this is the only thing you need.
```
public class MyClassEntity {
    @Column(name = &quot;content&quot;, columnDefinition = &quot;jsonb&quot;)
    @JdbcTypeCode(SqlTypes.JSON)
    private SubClass content;
}
```

For Hibernate 4 and 5, you need to implement `UserType` for it
```
public class SubClassType implements UserType&lt;SubClass&gt; {
 
    public static final ObjectMapper MAPPER = new ObjectMapper();
     
    @Override
    public int getSqlType() {
        return SqlTypes.JSON;
    }
 
    @Override
    public Class&lt;SubClass&gt; returnedClass() {
        return SubClass.class;
    }
 
    // implementations of nullSafeGet, deepCopy...
}
```
Also, declare it as `Custom type` on class level. This is the [documentation](https://thorben-janssen.com/persist-postgresqls-jsonb-data-type-hibernate/). I hope it helps.

